Kuwait’s Kharafi Group Sees Growth Potential in Middle East

-- B y   M a s s o u d   A .   D e r h a l l y   a n d   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 
2011-05-26T10:29:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/kuwait-s-kharafi-group-sees-growth-potential-in-middle-east.html
Kuwait ’s  Kharafi Group  sees potential
for expansion in  Saudi Arabia , Egypt, Qatar and the United Arab
Emirates, Vice President Marzouk Nasser Al-Kharafi said.  “There are a lot of opportunities and we will select
what’s the appropriate investment in light of current
developments in the region that are suitable,” Al-Kharafi said
in an interview in Beirut today. “There are opportunities in
the hundreds of millions” of dollars, he said.  The Kharafi Group has holdings in a number of companies
listed on the Kuwait Stock Exchange, including Mobile
Telecommunications Co., Kuwait’s biggest mobile-phone company,
and Kuwait Food Co.  The group has an annual turnover of more than $5 billion
and operates in more than 25 countries worldwide with activities
including construction, manufacturing, investment, tourism and
commerce, according to its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
